3. LAG DISTRIBUTION: MEDIATED vs NON-MEDIATED
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Hypothesis (Carpenter et al. 1998): shared affiliation compresses
  the adoption lag — signals travel faster through a live channel.

  Any-mediated (n=7)  vs  Non-mediated (n=3,340):
    Mean lag  — mediated: 1.86 q  |  non-mediated: 2.05 q
